<item>
            <title>[IO-679] input.AbstractCharacterFilterReader passes count of chars read to filter, not the filter char</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-679</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; &#160;Ran into a bug with&#160;AbstractCharacterFilterReader where I noticed that my filter was not receiving the actual characters, but was instead receiving an int value corresponding to the number of chars in my input stream buffer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I looked at&#160;the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-io/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/io/input/AbstractCharacterFilterReader.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;source file&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and realized that on line 64:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;if (filter(read)) {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 should have been:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;if (filter(cbuf&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;readPos&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;)) {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;read` has the number of chars read from the source reader, not the code point of the character read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a sample program that illustrates the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can work on a patch and submit it when done. I will add a test case in the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
